Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

== Burgers ==

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine half the garlic and the @British pork and oregano
sausage meat{225%grams}. Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick
burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a medium baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Tomato Sauce ==

Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Stir in the remaining @garlic cloves{1}(peeled and grated) and fry for
~{30%seconds}. Add the @tomato puree{30%grams} and stir fry for ~{1%minute},
then stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @sugar for the sauce{1/2%tsp}
and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.

Stir to combine, bring to the boil, then simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}.

When the tomato sauce has thickened, stir in the @butter{20%grams} and
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}. Taste the sauce and season. Add a
splash of water if it's a little too thick.

== Assembly ==

Halve the @sliced burger buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, share the burger buns between your #plates{}.

Top the bases with the sausage burgers and spoon over the sauce. Drizzle over the
@fresh pesto{32%grams}.

Sandwich together with the bun lids and serve with the chips alongside.

Enjoy!